  <!-- faq started -->
  <section class="text-center pt-36">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6 text-center">
      Frequently Asked Questions
    </h1>
    <h6>
      Explore our FAQs for clear insights on giving, eligibility, and the
      positive impact <br /> your contribution can make in transforming lives.
    </h6>
  </section>
  <section class="section-sm container max-w-2xl">
    <!-- ### Accordion -->

    <Accordion
      className="text-justify"
      client:load
      title="Who is eligible to receive Zakat?"
    >
      <p>
        Eight groups are eligible to receive Zakat:
        <ol
          class="max-w-md space-y-1 text-gray-500 list-decimal list-inside dark:text-gray-400"
        >
          <li>The poor</li>

          <li>The needy</li>
          <li>Administrators of Zakat</li>
          <li>Those with reconciled hearts</li>
          <li>Those who have been enslaved</li>
          <li>Those in debt</li>
          <li>In the cause of God</li>
          <li>Travellers (including refugees)</li>
        </ol>
        A poor person, not in your immediate family, whose excess property doesn't
        meet the nisab threshold is eligible to receive Zakat.
      </p>
    </Accordion>
    <Accordion
      className="text-justify"
      client:load
      title="When to Pay Zakat Online?"
    >
      <p>
        When your Zakat-eligible wealth surpasses the Nisab for a full lunar
        year, Zakat is due immediately. It becomes an annual obligation if your
        wealth remains above the Nisab.
      </p>
    </Accordion>
    <Accordion
      className="text-justify"
      client:load
      title="Why Give Your Zakat to Edhi Foundation?"
    >
      <p>
        Donate your Zakat with confidence through Edhi Foundation, ensuring it
        reaches where it's needed most. Trusted for over 30 years, our projects
        are Zakat-applicable, sustainable, and impactful.
      </p>
    </Accordion>
    <Accordion
      className="text-justify"
      client:load
      title="What part of my wealth is not Zakatable?"
    >
      <p>
        Items, except gold or silver not bought for resale, are not subject to
        Zakat. Personal belongings like a house or car are exempt from Zakat.
      </p>
    </Accordion>
  </section>

